title: Three Monarchs earn USA South recognition
text:
Three Monarchs earn USA South recognition A staff report 
Three Methodist athletes have been honored for their performances last week by the USA South Athletic Conference. 
Quarterback Dylan DeGroot was the freshman offensive rookie of the week. He was 22-for-35 passing for 322 yards and two touchdowns in a loss to Averett. He also rushed for a touchdown. Teammate Tevis Dasher, a linebacker, was the defensive rookie of the week after returning an interception for a score and notching two sacks. 
Sam Maxfield, a freshman from Pine Forest High, was the men's cross country rookie of the week.
